he%20relatively%20unknown%20Thompson%2C%20the%20fastest%20man%20this%20year%20with%20a%20best%20of%209.77sec%2C%20said%20he%20hadn't%20been%20%26quot%3Bfresh%20enough%26quot%3B%20over%20the%20final%2030%20metres.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20couldn't%20really%20see%20Lyles%2C%20I%20wasn't%20sure%2C%26quot%3B%2023-year-old%20Thompson%20said%20of%20the%20photo-finish.%20%26quot%3BIt%20was%20that%20close.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI'm%20going%20to%20take%20it%20and%20move%20forward%20from%20here%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BEverybody%20loves%20a%20winner%20so%20I%20would%20have%20loved%20to%20win%20today%2C%20but%20I%20loved%20the%20competition%20overall.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELyles'%20US%20teammate%20Fred%20Kerley%20took%20bronze%20in%209.81sec%2C%20just%20one-hundredth%20ahead%20of%20South%20African%20Akani%20Simbine%2C%20who%20timed%209.82sec.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20don't%20feel%20any%20frustration%20because%20I'm%20facing%20the%20best%20in%20the%20world%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Kerley%2C%20the%202022%20world%20champion%20and%20Olympic%20silver%20medallist%20over%20100m%20three%20years%20ago%20at%20the%20Tokyo%20Games.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAt%20the%20end%20of%20the%20day%2C%20not%20many%20people%20can%20say%20they%20came%20to%20the%20Olympic%20Games%2C%26quot%3B%20Kerley%20said.%20%26quot%3BWhoever%20came%20off%20the%20best%20is%20the%20best.%20It's%20my%20second%20time%20around%20and%20I'm%20going%20off%20with%20a%20medal.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20an%20astonishing%20race%2C%20defending%20champion%20Marcell%20Jacobs%20of%20Italy%20was%20fifth%20in%209.85sec%2C%20Botswana's%20Letsile%20Tebogo%20sixth%20in%209.86sec%2C%20American%20Kenny%20Bednarek%20seventh%20in%209.88sec%20and%20Jamaican%20Oblique%20Seville%20eighth%20in%209.91sec.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EStarting%20in%20lane%20seven%2C%20outside%20Seville%20and%20inside%20Tebogo%2C%20Lyles%20got%20off%20to%20an%20average%20start%20but%20was%20soon%20into%20his%20stride%20pattern.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHead%20tucked%20down%20through%20to%20the%2040-metre%20mark%2C%20the%20American%20opened%20up%2C%20but%20the%20whole%20field%20pushed%20him%20all%20the%20way.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20Lyles%20dipped%20for%20the%20line%20with%20Thompson%20charging%20alongside%20him%2C%20the%20crowd%20erupted%20and%20a%20photo-finish%20was%20called%20before%20Lyles%20was%20confirmed%20as%20gold%20medallist.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E-%20Tense%20buildup%20-%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThere%20was%20an%20electric%20pre-race%20atmosphere%20in%20a%2069%2C000-capacity%20Stade%20de%20France%2C%20a%20light%20show%20and%20booming%20music%20keeping%20the%20crowd%20entertained%20as%20the%20sprinters%20adjusted%20their%20starting%20blocks.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20lights%20then%20went%20off%20and%20the%20sprinters%20leaving%20the%20track%20to%20remake%20their%20entrance%20like%20prize%20fighters%20in%20a%20colosseum%2C%20with%20each%20sprinter%20individually%20introduced%20behind%20an%20image%20of%20their%20name%20above%20their%20flag.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThompson%20roared%2C%20hands%20clenched%20in%20fists%20as%20his%20head%20rolled%20back.%20Kerley%20patted%20his%20heart.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELyles%20bounded%20out%20like%20a%20kangaroo%2C%20bouncing%2020%20metres%20down%20the%20track.%20Jacobs%20was%20the%20definition%20of%20cool%2C%20raising%20both%20arms%20and%20calmly%20walking%20to%20his%20blocks.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThen%20came%20the%20moment%20where%20the%20sprinters%20set%2C%20at%20the%20starter's%20beck%20and%20call.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20wait%20seemed%20interminable.%20The%20music%20continued%2C%20the%20crowd%20clapped%20in%20unison%2C%20then%20the%20sprinters%20stood%20in%20their%20lanes%2C%20rocking%20from%20foot%20to%20foot%20and%20the%20tension%20was%20palpable%2C%20while%20the%20only%20sound%20was%20that%20of%20a%20helicopter%20whirring%20overhead.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20shot%20was%20fired%20and%20the%20field%20moved%20as%20if