st%2C%20around%2025%20to%2030%20percent%20of%20people%20with%20ASD%20(Autism%20Spectrum%20Disorder)%20are%20minimally%20verbal.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENow%2C%20I%20could%20convey%20the%20essence%20of%20non-speaking%20autism%20to%20you%20through%20research%20findings%2C%20news%20publishings%20and%20heavy%20jargon.%20But%20it%20wouldn%E2%80%99t%20do%20it%20justice.%20Instead%2C%20a%20sentence%20I%20read%20in%20an%20article%20published%20by%20the%20Organisation%20for%20Autism%20Research%20does%20the%20trick%20%E2%80%94%20%3Cem%3EImagine%20you%20answer%20everyone%20who%20says%20something%20to%20you%2C%20but%20only%20you%20can%20hear%20it.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWritten%20by%20Philip%20Reyes%2C%20an%20individual%20with%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthebetterindia.com%2F327878%2Fsejal-shah-mariposa-foundation-shares-lessons-for-raising-a-child-with-disability%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Enon-speaking%20autism%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20the%20article%20condemns%20the%20popular%20belief%20that%20non-speaking%20equals%20non-thinking.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAnd%20it%20is%20this%20very%20point%20that%20Padma%20Jyothi%20and%20Chitra%20Paul%20%E2%80%94%20both%20mothers%20to%20children%20with%20non-speaking%20autism%20%E2%80%94%20are%20driving%20home%20through%20their%20books%20Talking%20Fingers%20(2022)%20and%20Talking%20Fingers%20Volume%202%20(2024).%C2%A0%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3ESee%20their%20world%20for%20what%20it%20is%C2%A0%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3ESilence%20speaks%20louder%20than%20words.%C2%A0%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20compiling%20Talking%20Fingers%2C%20the%20meaning%20of%20this%20adage%20became%20clear%20to%20the%20mother%20duo%2C%20who%20refrain%20from%20calling%20themselves%20authors%20%E2%80%94%20%E2%80%9CWe%20have%20%3Cem%3Eedited%3C%2Fem%3E%20the%20book%3B%20they%20%5Bthe%2032%20individuals%5D%20are%20the%20real%20authors%E2%80%9D.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThrough%20their%20chapters%2C%20the%20books%20attempt%20to%20bust%20myths%20that%20have%20shadowed%20individuals%20with%20autism%20for%20decades.%20And%20this%20is%20done%20through%20a%20unique%20approach.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EInstead%20of%20a%20one-directional%20narrative%2C%20the%20books%20are%20a%20first-hand%20account%20of%20the%20challenges%2C%20hopes%20and%20dreams%20of%20people%20who%20belong%20to%20the%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthebetterindia.com%2F315291%2Fhyderabad-neena-rao-started-margika-foundation-for-neurodivergent-autism-care-support%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eneurodivergent%20spectrum%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Artists%2C%20writers%2C%20and%20publishers%2C%20these%2032%20individuals%20may%20have%20non-speaking%20autism%20but%20that%20hasn%E2%80%99t%20hindered%20them%20from%20making%20people%20sit%20up%20and%20take%20note%20of%20their%20words.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CDon%E2%80%99t%20eulogise%20us%2C%E2%80%9D%20is%20their%20only%20ask.%20%E2%80%9CWe%20are%20humans%20first%3B%20and%20people%20with%20autism%2C%20second.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EToday%2C%20the%20stage%20is%20theirs.%20Here%E2%80%99s%20what%20they%20want%20the%20world%2C%20you%20and%20me%20to%20know.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3E%E2%80%98Call%20us%20people%20with%20autism%3B%20not%20autistic%E2%80%99%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CPeople%20call%20us%20autistic%20as%20we%20can%E2%80%99t%20control%20our%20emotions.%20By%20that%20logic%2C%20so%20many%20humans%20cannot%20control%20their%20emotions.%20Does%20that%20mean%20they%20are%20all%20autistic%3F%E2%80%9D%20Sahana%20Singaravelan%20(13)%20writes.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAnd%20she%20makes%20a%20good%20argument.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20while%20the%20Chennai%20native%20has%20a%20bone%20to%20pick%20with%20those%20who%20call%20her%20%E2%80%98autistic%E2%80%99%2C%2020-year-old%20Satvik%20Sharma%20takes%20offence%20wit